│ *   `addSiblingLoops(ArrayRef<Loop *> NewLoops)`                                                                                                                                         │
│ *   `addChildLoops(ArrayRef<Loop *> NewLoops)`                                                                                                                                           │
│ *   `rerunPasses(Loop &L)`                                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ None of these methods directly correspond to "rebuilding a loop nest". The `LoopUnrollAndJamPass` operates on a `LoopNest` object. When it completely unrolls an inner loop, the         │
│ `LoopNest` object becomes stale because one of its constituent `Loop` objects is now invalid. The crash occurs when a subsequent pass tries to use this stale `LoopNest`.                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The `FunctionToLoopPassAdaptor` is responsible for creating `LoopNest` objects and running loop nest passes. If a pass invalidates the nest, the adaptor needs to be informed so it can  │
