│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Looking at the available API, `rerunPasses(Loop &L)` seems the most promising. It is described as a way to "completely restart the loop pass pipeline for a given loop". By restarting   │
│ the pipeline for the outermost loop of the nest, we would force the `FunctionToLoopPassAdaptor` to re-evaluate the loop structure, which should include rebuilding the `LoopNest` from   │
│ the now-modified loop hierarchy. This is an expensive operation, as the comment notes, but it's necessary here because the fundamental structure on which the pass operates has been     │
│ invalidated.                                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
