│ The previous attempts to fix the crash failed due to compilation errors, revealing my misunderstanding of the `LPMUpdater` API. Neither `rebuildLoopNest` nor `rerunPasses` exist on     │
│ that class.                                                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fundamental problem is analysis invalidation. The `LoopUnrollAndJamPass` modifies the loop structure, invalidating the `LoopNest` object it received. However, the pass incorrectly  │
│ tells the pass manager that it *preserves* the `LoopNestAnalysis`. When the pass is run a second time, the pass manager provides the same, now-stale, `LoopNest` object, leading to the  │
│ crash.                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The correct solution within the new Pass Manager framework is to properly declare which analyses are invalidated. If the `LoopUnrollAndJamPass` modifies the loop nest, it must not      │
│ claim to preserve `LoopNestAnalysis`.                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The current implementation of `LoopUnrollAndJamPass::run` is:                                                                                                                            │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│   if (!tryToUnrollAndJamLoop(LN, ..., U))                                                                                                                                                │
│     return PreservedAnalyses::all();                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│   auto PA = getLoopPassPreservedAnalyses();                                                                                                                                              │
│   PA.preserve<LoopNestAnalysis>(); // This is the incorrect line                                                                                                                         │
│   return PA;                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ When `tryToUnrollAndJamLoop` returns `true` (indicating a modification), the pass explicitly preserves `LoopNestAnalysis`. This is wrong. By removing the line                           │
│ `PA.preserve<LoopNestAnalysis>();`, the pass will correctly signal that the analysis is invalidated. This will force the `FunctionToLoopPassAdaptor` to re-run `LoopNestAnalysis` before │
│ executing the next pass that requires it, thus providing a fresh and valid `LoopNest`.                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
